itemDescription: Royal Navy commander and Governor of the Gambia

wikipedia_page.main: Henry Froude Seagram (c. July 1802 – 26 August 1843) was Lieutenant Governor of the Gambia from January 1843 and Governor from June 1843 to 26 August 1843 when he died there of fever.
